Art,<br>
     Finally made it to your site, and from there to Tom Dier's. Liked what I saw. Big Red 1, huh? All my instructors at Benning wore that on their right shoulder.<br><br>
Tom,<br>
     Especially liked your humor section. On trading for air conditioners, the going rate in late '68 with the Air Force guys at Phu Cat was 5 AK47s = 1 air conditioner. The real difficult prize was plastic toilet seats.<br><br>
     Before going on active duty, I spent almost 23 years in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. Am a certified Packer Backer &amp; cheesehead. Know the territory you covered well. Draw a line from Prairie du Chien through Green Bay, and I've been on practically every other road between it and the Illinois border.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


